  "part3": {
    "proposedNetworkDataUrl": null,
    "proposedNetworkDesc": "NCWTR's target network architecture consolidates the current 17-silo infrastructure into a unified hub-and-spoke model with the Central Office as the primary hub and each regional office as a resilient spoke. All 17 regional offices will be connected via dedicated fiber (≥100 Mbps) or fixed wireless broadband, replacing DSL and LTE connections. The Central Office will upgrade to dual 1 Gbps fiber links with automatic failover. A government cloud environment (GovCloud PH) will host the UQMP and CFCP, with a secondary disaster recovery node at the DICT GovCloud DR site in Davao City — the first time NCWTR has had a disaster recovery plan that does not consist of the phrase \"call the ICT Director.\"",
